  1→/**
  2→ * Acceptance Tests: Tool Governance (US-8)
  3→ *
  4→ * Walking skeleton phase 9: Policies are attachable to tools via governs_tool
  5→ * relation edges. The proxy evaluates governance policies before executing
  6→ * integration tool calls. Policy check happens BEFORE credential resolution.
  7→ *
  8→ * Traces: US-8, FR-10, AC-8
  9→ * Driving port: POST /proxy/llm/anthropic/v1/messages (step 8.5 governance path)
 10→ *
 11→ * Implementation sequence:
 12→ *   1. Walking skeleton: policy denies tool call with reason  [ENABLED]
 13→ *   2. Policy denial writes trace with denial reason
 14→ *   3. Policy with max_per_day limit enforced
 15→ *   4. Tool with no governs_tool edge proceeds normally
 16→ *   5. Multiple policies evaluated (most restrictive wins)
 17→ *   6. Rate limit enforced via can_use.max_calls_per_hour
 18→ *   7. Rate limited call writes trace with rate_limited outcome
